      <p>Ever wondered what’s running the show behind your favorite website? In the wild world of digital experiences, knowing the Content Management System (CMS) powering a site is like holding the keys to the kingdom. Meet <strong>CRFT Lookup</strong>, your techy sidekick that sniffs out CMS platforms and more with just a URL and a wink.</p>
      <p>With hundreds of CMS options out there—from old-school WordPress to sleek headless systems like Contentful—figuring out what’s under the hood used to require a tech wizard’s hat. Not anymore. CRFT Lookup spills the beans on any website’s tech stack, CMS included, faster than you can say “digital detective.”</p>

      <h2>Why CMS Sleuthing Matters</h2>
      <p>Before we dive into how CRFT Lookup works its magic, let’s break down why CMS detection is a game-changer:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Competitor Recon</strong>: Curious about how rivals build their sites? Their CMS choice reveals their strategy—flexibility, scalability, or maybe just sticking to the classics.</li>
        <li><strong>Beginner’s Blueprint</strong>: New to web-building? See what top sites use and kickstart your project with a proven platform.</li>
        <li><strong>Pro Moves</strong>: Developers and agencies, this is your jam. Spot CMS trends and make data-driven recommendations that leave clients in awe.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>CRFT Lookup doesn’t just say, “Yup, it’s Drupal.” It delivers a full tech rundown—free, fast, and with a dash of charm.</p>

      <h2>How CRFT Lookup Cracks the Code</h2>
      <p>So, how does CRFT Lookup play CMS detective? Picture it as a cyber-sleuth, combing through a site’s HTML, JavaScript, response headers, and more. Armed with a database of over 2,500 technology fingerprints, it fires up a headless Chromium instance to scan any URL you toss its way. In mere seconds, it pins down CMS platforms like WordPress, Webflow, or Shopify, plus other tech like frameworks and analytics tools.</p>
      <p>Pop in a website’s URL, and CRFT Lookup hunts for CMS clues left in public-facing code. It’s not limited to CMS either—it can dissect any site, from Stripe to PostHog, serving up a tidy tech stack summary that’s easy on the eyes.</p>

      <h2>Beyond CMS: The Ultimate Tech Takedown</h2>
      <p>CRFT Lookup isn’t here to do the bare minimum. It goes all-in, giving you a panoramic view of a website’s tech profile. Here’s the full scoop:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tech Stack Breakdown</strong>: Spot everything from React and Gatsby to Cloudflare and AWS. It’s the whole tech enchilada.</li>
        <li><strong>Lighthouse Scores</strong>: Google Lighthouse metrics rate performance, accessibility, SEO, and best practices. Is that site speedy or just sparkly? Find out.</li>
        <li><strong>Meta Tag Previews</strong>: Check how a site looks when shared on Google, Twitter, or WhatsApp. Make sure its social vibe is pure fire.</li>
        <li><strong>Sitemap Visualization</strong>: Dive into a site’s structure with an interactive tree view, mapping out pages and navigation like a digital treasure hunt.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Whether you’re sizing up a competitor’s CMS or analyzing a site’s performance, these insights let you spot weaknesses, borrow brilliance (ethically!), and level up your game.</p>

      <h2>Real-World Superpowers</h2>
      <p>What can you <em>do</em> with this tech intel? Oh, plenty:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Business Owners</strong>: Compare CMS choices to industry leaders and pick the perfect platform for your site.</li>
        <li><strong>Marketers</strong>: Understand which CMS powers top campaigns in your niche and tailor your strategy.</li>
        <li><strong>Developers</strong>: Uncover CMS patterns and integrations to build sharper, smarter solutions.</li>
        <li><strong>Agencies</strong>: Walk into client pitches with tech insights that scream “We’ve got this.”</li>
      </ul>
