      <h2>Keeping It Ethical (and Free!)</h2>
      <p>Let’s clear the air: CRFT Lookup only pokes around in publicly accessible data. No hacking into private code or spilling sensitive secrets—it’s all legit, just reading what’s out in the open. Think of it as checking the ingredients on a cereal box, not raiding the kitchen.</p>
      <p>And yes, it’s <em>free</em>. Unlimited scans, no strings attached. How do they make money? By offering top-tier web design and development services, not by charging for reports. Share your findings via unique URLs, stored for 30 days, and packed with all the details—perfect for team collabs or client flexes.</p>

      <h2>The Fine Print on CMS Detection</h2>
      <p>To keep things straight: CRFT Lookup doesn’t dish out detailed CMS feature lists, use cases, or technical requirements. It identifies platforms (like WordPress or Contentful) and categorizes them based on their technical footprints. Want more? You’ll need to dig into the CMS yourself—CRFT just hands you the map.</p>
      <p>Its detection is rock-solid, thanks to a constantly updated engine that cross-checks multiple clues. That said, it can only spot CMS platforms with public-facing signatures—super-custom or hidden setups might stay off the radar.</p>

      <h2>Ready to Snoop?</h2>
      <p>Whether you’re a business owner picking a CMS, a developer chasing tech inspiration, or just a web-curious soul, CRFT Lookup is your ticket to uncovering the tech behind any site. Run a scan, share the results, and build smarter. You might just stumble on the secret sauce that turns your site from “okay” to “outstanding.”</p>
